  <title translate="true">SUTRA Boundary Condition Panes</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">SUTRA Boundary Condition Panes</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">There are four SUTRA boundary condition panes on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SUTRA_Features_Tab" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Sutra Features</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab of the &#160;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Object_Properties_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Object Properties</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box:</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Specified Head</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Specified Pressure,</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Specified Concentration</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Specified Pressure,</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Fluid Flux</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">, and</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Mass Flux</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true"> or</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true"> Energy Flux</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:normal;" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">SUTRA boundary condition panes are only visible if </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Properties_Tab" anchor="EvaluatedAt" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Evaluated at</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is set to </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Nodes</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Schedule (BCSSCH)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> combobox is used to select a </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SUTRA_Time_Controls_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">time schedule</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and a table where the boundary condition values are defined. The user can select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Custom</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> as the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SUTRA_Time_Controls_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">time schedule</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. With a </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Custom</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> time schedule, the user can specify any time in the boundary condition table. Otherwise, only times defined in the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="SUTRA_Time_Controls_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">time schedule</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can be selected.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The boundary condition table has either three or four columns depending on the type of boundary condition to be defined. The first column is always used to specify a </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Time</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. This is a time at which the boundary condition changes. The second column (</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Used</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">) turns the boundary condition on or off. The remaining columns vary depending on what type of boundary condition is being defined. However, they always contain </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Formulas" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">formulas</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> defining the boundary condition. For example with a specified pressure boundary condition, the user would define formulas for the specified pressure and the associated concentration. Above the table is an edit box that can be used to specify several formulas at once, To use it select two or more cells in the table where formulas are defined and then enter a formula in the edit box. The formula will be copied to the selected cells.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The user is not required to specify a change in the boundary condition for every time step in the schedule. Only times at which there is a change need to be included in the table.</text></para>
  </body>
